18/07/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Regional co-operation is key to integration into Euro-Atlantic structures, agreed Croatian President Stipe Mesic and his Macedonian counterpart, Boris Trajkovski.
The Macedonian head of state arrived on a three-day visit to Zagreb Thursday (17 July).
Describing Croatia's progress as "encouraging and inspirational", he said Macedonia is planning to submit an official application for EU membership by the end of this year.
According to media reports, Croatia is determined to join Bulgaria and Romania in seeking EU membership in 2007.
(Vest, MediaScan - 18/07/03;
HINA, MIA, BBC, A1 TV - 17/07/03)
